Company Overview of Ecoark Holdings, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Ecoark Holdings, Inc., a diversified holding company, engages in the development and deployment of business solutions and products to the retail, agriculture, and food service markets. Its portfolio of proprietary, patented technologies address the waste in operations, logistics, and supply chain. The company, through its subsidiary, Pioneer Products, LLC, recycles plastics from reclaimed retailers’ waste streams; remanufactures into new consumer products, such as plastic trash cans; and sells products in the retail market. Ecoark Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiary, Zest Labs, Inc., provides farmers, distributors, and grocers a freshness management solution focused on reducing food waste...
Ecoark Holdings, Inc., a diversified holding company, engages in the development and deployment of business solutions and products to the retail, agriculture, and food service markets. Its portfolio of proprietary, patented technologies address the waste in operations, logistics, and supply chain. The company, through its subsidiary, Pioneer Products, LLC, recycles plastics from reclaimed retailers’ waste streams; remanufactures into new consumer products, such as plastic trash cans; and sells products in the retail market. Ecoark Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiary, Zest Labs, Inc., provides farmers, distributors, and grocers a freshness management solution focused on reducing food waste. Its flagship product is Zest Fresh, which combines real-time prescriptive analytics with IoT product-level monitoring to enable proactive and intelligent decision-making at every step of the fresh food supply chain from field to shelf. The company, through its subsidiary, Magnolia Solar Inc., engages in the development, production, and sale of nanotechnology-based thin film solar cell modules. Ecoark Holdings, Inc. was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Rogers, Arkansas.
